vectorData.altText: 13. Identify cardiac muscle tissue in longitudinal section and click on the letter of the corresponding image below.
That's right!  Diagram C represents cardiac muscle tissue in longitudinal section. Notice the striations, branching of cells and the intercalated discs.
That is incorrect. Click here      to learn the answer, then come back to try again.
Skeletal muscle: striated, straight, multinucleate cells. Nuclei peripherally located. Nuclei small relative to the cell.
Cardiac muscle: striated, branching mononucleate cells joined at intercalated discs. Nuclei centrally located. Nuclei proportionate to the cell size.
Smooth muscle: nonstriated, tapering, mononucleate cells. Nuclei centrally located. In cross section, the nuclei of many cells are not seen. Nuclei, when seen, are large relative to the cell.
